Reducing the Good to ethics. The Good is also the condition of truth, knowledge, and being-known.
Treating Book X as anti-art cliché. Better: Plato knows images shape the soul and therefore treats them as spiritually dangerous.
Forgetting the Myth of Er’s choice structure. Fate is not simple determinism; the soul chooses under cosmic law and prior habit.
