Homeric/cosmic geography of gates
zodiacal/solstitial descent-ascent symbolism
Bees/honey can split into:
bees as souls
honey as ritual nourishment
Overlap warnings
Porphyry’s cave vs Plato’s Cave: related but not identical. Plato’s Cave is epistemological captivity; Porphyry’s cave is cosmic generation and initiatory transit.
Symbolism vs free association: Porphyry is not making a moodboard. He anchors symbols in Homer, Plato, myth, cult, cosmology, and etymology.
Mithraic comparison: useful but handle carefully; do not make Porphyry’s Homeric cave simply “a Mithras temple.”
Odysseus as soul: do not erase the literary Odysseus. The allegory works because the narrative remains vivid.
Nymphs: do not reduce them to “feminine energy.” In Porphyry, they are specific powers of watery generation.
Missing-content review

Potential weak spots:

Skipping the vessels and weaving. These details make the cave a generative workshop, not just an empty chamber.
