Flattening the two gates. They are the structural key: the cave is a passage-system, not just a room.
Treating Athena’s olive tree as decorative. Its placement outside the cave is metaphysically important.
Forgetting Odysseus. The treatise is not only about symbols; it is about homecoming through symbolic reality.
