Best Imaginarium use

Porphyry’s On the Cave of the Nymphs should become Imaginarium’s source for symbolic image-reading as metaphysical cartography.

Its clean system formula:

a cave is not just a cave → the world is a chamber of generation → bodies are woven vessels → souls move like bees through sweetness and purification → the cosmos has gates of descent and ascent → wisdom stands outside the cave as Athena’s olive tree → Odysseus is the soul returning home through symbolic reality.

This is an ideal bridge from Plato and Plotinus into later esotericism because it shows exactly how a mythic image becomes a full cosmological interface.

