Overlap warnings
Apuleius vs Plato’s Symposium: Plato gives Eros as daimonic mediator; Apuleius generalizes mediation into a daimonic class.
Apuleius vs Phaedrus: Phaedrus dramatizes Socrates’ daimonic interruption; Apuleius theorizes what such a being is.
Apuleius vs Greenbaum: Apuleius is not doing Hellenistic astrology technique; Greenbaum can later bridge daimon with lots/houses/ruling planet.
Daimon vs modern “inner voice”: do not psychologize too quickly. Apuleius’ daimon is cosmological, not merely subjective.
Daimon vs demon: avoid Christianized horror framing. Use “daimon” when possible to preserve the Platonic sense.
