Ignoring the aerial body. This is one of the strangest and most useful details.
Making Socrates’ daimon purely positive. Its guidance is often prohibitive.
Skipping ethics. Daimonic hearing depends on the quality of the receiver.
Over-importing astrology. Keep Apuleius clean, then bridge to Greenbaum later.
