Companion Blueprint 10 — Proclus’ Elements of Theology
Source identification

Work: Proclus, Elements of Theology
Author: Proclus, 412–485 CE
Stream: late Neoplatonic metaphysics, hierarchy, participation, procession, reversion, henads, intellect, soul
Structure: 211 propositions, each followed by a proof. Public summaries identify it as a systematic compendium of Neoplatonic metaphysics.


Public access: Taylor’s older public-domain translation is available online; Dodds’ critical edition is accessible in some online archives, but use cautiously and avoid long quotation.

Why this matters for Imaginarium:
If Plotinus gives emanation and return, Proclus gives the fully engineered metaphysical machine:

One → henads → being → life → intellect → soul → embodied descent → all things proceed from their causes → remain in them → return toward them.

This is Imaginarium’s source for ontological architecture.

Structural map
Proposition zone	Function	Imaginarium use
1–6	Unity and multiplicity	Everything many depends on unity.
7–13	Causality and productivity	Causes exceed effects.
14–20	Participation	Lower things share in higher principles.
21–39	Procession and reversion	Everything proceeds and returns.
40–52	Self-constitution	Higher beings are self-grounded.
