Refined essay sequence
1. The Many Cannot Explain Themselves

Passages: props. 1–6
Plan:

Start with multiplicity.
Show why every many depends on unity.
Relate this to perception: a world appears only because it is unified.
Imaginarium angle: rendering requires coherence before content.
2. The Source Is More Than Its Image

Passages: props. 7–13
Plan:

Cause exceeds effect.
Effects disclose causes but cannot contain them.
This grounds symbolic humility.
Imaginarium angle: never confuse the rendered icon with the source.
3. Participation: How the Higher Is Present Below

Passages: props. 14–20
Plan:

Explain participation without reducing it to metaphor.
A lower thing can share in a higher principle.
This becomes the metaphysics of sacred image, planetary influence, and soul.
Bridge to Proclus’ later theurgic world.
4. Remaining, Proceeding, Returning

Passages: props. 21–39
Plan:

The core triad: every effect remains in its cause, proceeds from it, and returns to it.
This is not linear only; it is ontological circulation.
Imaginarium angle: all practice is reversion after procession.
5. The Self-Constituted Being

Passages: props. 40–52
Plan:

Some realities do not derive their identity from outside.
Self-constitution marks a higher ontological level.
Use carefully with intelligence/agency themes.
Bridge to Levin only later, not inside the Proclus essay.
6. Eternity Is Not Endless Time

Passages: props. 53–65
Plan:

Eternal things exist whole-at-once.
Temporal things unfold by before and after.
Soul mediates between these modes.
Imaginarium angle: time is a rendered unfolding of higher simultaneity.
7. The Henads: Divine Unity in Plural Form

Passages: props. 66–112
Plan:

Introduce the gods as henads.
Each god is a unity beyond intellect.
Divine plurality does not break the One; it expresses unitary sources.
Imaginarium angle: archetypal plurality must be grounded in metaphysics, not mood.
8. Being, Life, Intellect

Passages: props. 113–165
Plan:

Map the noetic architecture.
Being gives stability; Life gives self-movement; Intellect gives self-knowing form.
This is the living architecture behind reality.
Imaginarium angle: the source-realm is alive intelligence, not abstraction.
9. Soul as the Rendering Mediator

Passages: props. 166–183
Plan:

Soul receives intellect and unfolds it into motion/time/life.
Soul is between indivisible and divisible.
This is the metaphysical basis for imagination, world-order, and embodiment.
Bridge to Timaeus world soul.
10. The Descent and Return of Particular Souls

Passages: props. 184–211
Plan:

Individual souls descend into body.
They remain connected to higher causes.
Return is possible because procession never severs remaining.
Imaginarium angle: the soul can re-render itself because it never fully lost its source.
