Potential gaps:

Ignoring the frame. Proclus spends serious work on the opening; do not jump straight to Demiurge.
Underusing world soul. This is the most important Imaginarium zone.
Skipping celestial gods. This is the bridge to objective astrology.
Forgetting the extant limit. The commentary stops at 44d; receptacle/elemental geometry need other sources.
Using Taylor uncritically. Taylor is public-domain but old; modern editions are better for scholarship.
