Cut / merge / split decisions

Keep separate:

“Why myths hide truth” and “five kinds of myth.” One explains concealment; the other gives taxonomy.
Providence/fate/fortune and ritual. One is cosmic causality; the other is participatory response.
Gods and myths. Gods are ontology; myths are symbolic speech about ontology.

