Overlap warnings
Sallustius vs Proclus: Proclus builds metaphysical machinery; Sallustius gives compact theological pedagogy.
Sallustius vs Porphyry: Porphyry performs symbolic reading on one Homeric image; Sallustius gives general myth-reading rules.
Sallustius vs Hermetica: Hermetica is revelatory gnosis; Sallustius is philosophical pagan theology.
Myth vs allegory: do not make myth “just code.” Myth is symbolic concealment that transforms the reader.
Ritual: do not reduce sacrifice to primitive bargaining. Sallustius explicitly supports a higher philosophical reading.
